# Copy to .env for local runs.
# Hybrid (hot reload on host): `npm run dev:all` — only Postgres in Docker; migrations + seed on host; Next + Nest via `concurrently` on :3000 / :4000.
# Full stack in Docker from scratch (wipe volumes, rebuild images, wait for health): `npm run docker:stack:fresh` — postgres, backend (migrate+seed+dev), frontend (next dev). Then open http://localhost:3000
# Root `npm run dev` / `dev:all:app` run `dev:kill-ports` first (3000, 4000) to avoid EADDRINUSE from a previous Next/Nest process.
# dev:all loads `docker.local.env` via env-cmd so Prisma/Nest use the same URL as compose.
# If `prisma migrate deploy` fails with syntax error near U+FEFF, migration SQL was saved with UTF-8 BOM (e.g. PowerShell Out-File -Encoding utf8); use UTF-8 without BOM or rewrite the file in the editor.
# If Prisma still fails with P1010 after changing POSTGRES_* in compose, the old Docker volume may have a different DB user — run `npm run docker:db:reset` once, then `npm run dev:all`.
# For manual `npm run dev` without dev:all, align DATABASE_URL with docker.local.env (127.0.0.1, cinema/cinema, sslmode=disable).
# Re-run seed on non-empty DB: SEED_FORCE=true npm run db:seed -w backend (wipes movies/halls/seats/sessions/reservations).
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://cinema:cinema@127.0.0.1:5432/cinema?schema=public

JWT_SECRET=replace-with-long-random-string
# Access token TTL (e.g. 15m, 7d). Passed to jsonwebtoken.
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d

FRONTEND_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000

# Set to "true" behind a reverse proxy so rate limits use X-Forwarded-For correctly.
# TRUST_PROXY=true

# Optional. Hold duration for new reservations in ms (default 300000 = 5 minutes).
# RESERVATION_HOLD_MS=300000

PORT=4000
